title: FEC | Legal resources | Enforcement
description: The Federal Election Commission has jurisdiction over the civil enforcement of the federal campaign finance law. Enforcement cases can come from audits, complaints, referrals or self-submissions: Enforcement cases are primarily handled by the Office of General Counsel and are known as Matters Under Review (MURs). Other programs designed to augment the Office of General Counsel's enforcement role include the Alternative Dispute Resolution Program and the Administrative Fine Program.
